The ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has pegged its expression of interest and nomination forms for the Anambra State governorship election at N22.5 million. The party has equally fixed its primary election for June 26, ahead of the November poll. APC’s Director of Organisation, Prof Usijju Medaner Al-Mustapha, disclosed this in a statement on Thursday, in Abuja. According to the statement, sales of forms commenced on April 14 and would end on June 8, which is also the last day for the submission of forms. Screening of aspirants, according to the party, would begin on June 10 while publication of claims and objections would hold on June 12. “Female aspirants and persons living with disabilities are however to pay 50 per cent of the prescribed fees,” the party said.